1️⃣ Create a Dockerfile:-
nano Dockerfile

Paste this content inside:
# Use official Python base image
FROM python:3.11-slim

# Set working directory inside the container
WORKDIR /app

# Copy the Python script into the container
COPY main1.py .

# Command to run the script
CMD ["python", "main1.py"]
-FROM python:3.11-slim → Uses lightweight Python 3.11 image
-WORKDIR /app → Sets /app as the working folder inside the container
-COPY main1.py . → Copies your Python file into the container
-CMD ["python", "main1.py"] → Runs your script when the container starts
-Save and exit (Ctrl+O, Enter, Ctrl+X in nano).

2️⃣ Build the Docker image:-
docker build -t my-python-app .
-t my-python-app → gives your image a name (my-python-app)
. → tells Docker to look for the Dockerfile in the current directory
You should see Docker download the Python image and copy your file.

3️⃣ Run the Docker container
docker run my-python-app

You should see the output of your script:
